survey_id: Add a unique number for each row
Site_id: Should match exactly with the 'Site_id' in the time series metadata and - if vegetation surveys are available - with the 'Site_id' in the 'vegetation data'
Survey_method_short: Short description of the sampling method
Survey_method_long: Long description of the sampling as it appears in the M&M section
Multilayer vegetation: Where several canopy layer recorded (e.g. understory, tree ...)? Yes or NO
Taxonomic reference: Taxonomical reference used to identify the species
Species richness: Number of vascular plant species in the plot
Other: If other variables are measured at plot level, they can be added here and their units defined can be defined accordingly in 'Other unit'. Feel free to add more 'other'-columns
DOI: DOI of the vegetation data, if available
Licence:
Creative Commons license for your data. Open Acces: CC0, Open Acces with credit to the authors CC-BY, access after validation by the authors C) - https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Creative_Commons_license

If in doubt, choose CC-BY
